'''ChucK''' 是一个并发和强调时间的[[音频编程语言列表|音频编程语言]]，主要用于实时[[合成器|声音合成]]、作曲和表演，<ref name=collins_rincon2007>{{cite book
 | author=Ge Wang
 | editor=Collins, Nicholas; Rincón, Julio d'Escrivan
 | chapter=A history of programming and music
 | title=The Cambridge companion to electronic music
 | publisher=Cambridge University Press
 | year=2007
 | isbn=0-521-86861-0
 | page=69
 | url=http://books.google.com/books?id=AJbdPZv1DjgC&pg=PA69
 | access-date=2013-11-22
 | archive-date=2014-01-03
 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140103120056/http://books.google.com/books?id=AJbdPZv1DjgC&pg=PA69
 | dead-url=no
 }}</ref> 可运行于[[OS_X|OS X]]、[[Linux|Linux]]、[[Microsoft_Windows|Microsoft Windows]]和 [[iOS|iOS]]。相比性能等其他因素的考虑，它的设计更注重程序的可读性与编程灵活性。它原生支持确定性[[并发|并发]]和同时多重动态控制率。另外一个关键的功能其对{{link-en|现场编程|Live coding}}的支持， 可以在程序不停止或重启的情况下，现场增加、删除和修改程序。它有着非常精确的定时/并发模型，允许任意准确的控制。它为作曲家与研究人员而开发的编程工具兼具强大性能与灵活性，包括对复杂[[合成器|声音合成]]进行开发和调试，以及实时的交互控制。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://chuck.cs.princeton.edu/ |title=ChucK : Strongly-timed, Concurrent, and On-the-fly Music Programming Language |deadurl=yes |accessdate=2013-09-06 |quote=...offers composers, researchers, and performers a powerful programming tool for building and experimenting with complex audio synthesis/analysis programs, and real-time interactive music. |archive-date=2011-04-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110410221042/http://chuck.cs.princeton.edu/ }}</ref>

== 代码例子 ==
下面是生成声音和音乐一个简单的ChucK程序：

  <span style="color:#339933;">// our signal graph (patch)</span>
  SinOsc f => dac;
  <span style="color:#339933;">// set gain</span>
  .3 => f.gain;
  <span style="color:#339933;">// an array of pitch classes (in half steps)</span>
  [ 0, 2, 4, 6, 9, 10 ] @=> <span style="color:blue;">int</span> hi[];
  
  <span style="color:#339933;">// infinite loop</span>
  <span style="color:blue;">while</span>( <span style="color:blue;">true</span> )
  {
      <span style="color:#339933;">// choose a note, shift registers, convert to frequency</span>
      Std.mtof( 65 + Std.rand2(0,1) * 43 +
          hi[Std.rand2(0,hi.cap()-1)] ) => f.freq;
  
      <span style="color:#339933;">// advance time by 120 ms</span>
      120::<span style="color:blue;">ms</span> => <span style="color:blue;">now</span>;
  }

